-- Nigeria Diamond Bank to sell between $300 mln-$350 mln Eurobond
-- By Chijioke Ohuocha
-- Tue May 13, 2014 01:18PM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, May 13 (Reuters) - Nigeria's Diamond Bank <DIAMONB.LG> is in the Eurobond market to issue between $300 million to $350 million of debt and has commenced a deal roadshow to sell the bond, its chief financial  officer told Reuters on Tuesday.

"It would be a benchmark issue, anything between $300 million and $350 million," Abdulraham Yinusa said. Citigroup is marketing the bond and has organised roadshows to Britain and the United States. Bankers expect the bond, which has a five-year maturity, to be priced on Wednesday at an 8 to 9 percent yield.